<sect1 id="GetFileDescription">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>GetFileDescription</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <!-- DNT-Start --><para><emphasis role="bold">STD.File.GetFileDescription<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.File.GetFileDescription</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>File.GetFileDescription</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>GetFileDescription</primary>
    </indexterm>( </emphasis> <emphasis>filename </emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para><!-- DNT-End -->

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>filename</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>A null-terminated string containing the logical name of the
          file.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->Return:<emphasis> </emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->GetFileDescription<!-- DNT-End --> returns a <!-- DNT-Start -->VARSTRING<!-- DNT-End --> (null-terminated)
          value.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->GetFileDescription<!-- DNT-End --> </emphasis>function
  returns a string containing the description information stored by the <!-- DNT-Start -->DFU<!-- DNT-End -->
  about the specified <emphasis>filename</emphasis>. This description is set
  either through <!-- DNT-Start -->ECL<!-- DNT-End --> watch or by using the <!-- DNT-Start -->STD<!-- DNT-End -->.File.SetFileDescription
  function.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting format="linespecific">A := STD.File.GetFileDescription('Fred');</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->
</sect1>
